explanation:
Command: @atrcache[/switch(es)] <cachename/slot> [=<target/value>]

  The @atrcache command is ued to cache out the EXECUTION of a string so
  that it won't have to keep evaluating this until the next interval 
  specified.  This is intended to be used for heavy use cases where
  execution of code can have a huge performance hit or on something
  that would be called intensely in a loop that could also cause delay,
  lage, or intensive loads.

  The maximum caches are handled by a config parameter.  10 default
  with an absolute maximum being 200.

  On system start (or reboot) all caches are unitialized and any
  cached values will have been cleared.

  The following switches exist for the command.  Individual help is
  availalbe for each one.
      @atrcache/init <cacheslot> = <name to use>
        -- initialize the cache slot for use.
      @atrcache/delete <cacheslot/cachename>
        -- uninitialize and deallocate cache slot.
      @atrcache/name <cacheslot or cachename> = <newname>
        -- rename the specified cache slot.
      @atrcache/owner <cacheslot or cachename> = <new owner>
        -- specify the new owner for the specified cache slot.
      @atrcache/visible <cacheslot or cachename> = <boolean>
        -- toggle if the cache slot is globally avaialble to fetch
      @atrcache/lock <cacheslot or cachename> = <boolean>
        -- toggle enforcing of recaching by owner or control.
      @atrcache/fetch <cacheslot or cachename>
        -- fetch the cache (useful for testing)
      @atrcache/interval <cacheslot or cachename> = <value>
        -- specify the new interval for recaching the cache
      @atrcache/cache <cacheslot or cachename>
        -- force recache the specified cache slot
      @atrcache/list [0 for all, or page value]
        -- give overview summary of all cache slots
      @atrcache/info[/noansi] <cacheslot or cachename>
        -- give detailed information of the specified cache.
      @atrcache/set <cacheslot or cachename> = <evaluated string>
        -- assign the cache slot the string to be executed for caching
      @atrcache/noansi  
        -- used with the /info switch to supress ansi output

  Indivitual help is available on each switch with 'help @atrcache/switchname'

  See Also: atrcache(), %-h

